[2026-03-18T18:31:04.952Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CxroRcNq3gPEPrZ489cQLJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored your codebase and compiled detailed findings across all the key systems you requested.\n\n### 1. AUDIT LOG SYSTEM\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n\n**Database Schema**:\n- Table: `audit_events` with columns:\n  - `id` (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n  - `timestamp` (TEXT NOT NULL) - ISO 8601 format\n  - `action` (TEXT NOT NULL) - string literal from AuditAction type\n  - `tenant_id` (TEXT) - optional tenant identifier\n  - `actor` (TEXT) - user email or projectId\n  - `resource_type` (TEXT) - entity type being audited\n  - `resource_id` (TEXT) - ID of affected resource\n  - `detail` (TEXT) - JSON-stringified detail object\n  - `ip_address` (TEXT) - remote IP from request\n  - `prev_hash` (TEXT) - SHA-256 chain hash for integrity verification\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_audit_ts` on `timestamp`\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` on `(tenant_id, action, timestamp)`\n\n**Key Features**:\n- **Buffered writes**: 50-entry buffer or 100ms flush interval (reduces fsync overhead)\n- **SHA-256 hash chain**: Each entry commits to entire history before it via `computeChainHash()`\n- **Genesis value**: 64 hex zeros for the first hash (deterministic)\n- **Chain verification**: `verify()` method validates entire chain integrity\n- **Migration support**: Auto-adds missing `prev_hash` column to existing DBs\n\n**Audit Entry Types** (discriminated union):\n- Key management: `key:encrypt`, `key:decrypt`, `key:decrypt_failed`, `key:delete`, `key:access`, `key:derive`\n- Personas: `persona:create`, `persona:delete`\n- Tools: `tool:link`, `tool-definition:create`\n- Credentials: `credential:link`\n- Subscriptions: `subscription:create`, `subscription:update`, `subscription:delete`\n- Workers: `worker:connected`, `worker:disconnected`\n- Triggers: `trigger:create`, `trigger:update`, `trigger:delete`\n- Events: `event:publish`, `event:update`\n- Executions: `execution:submit`\n- Webhooks: `webhook:receive`\n\n**Query Method**: `query({ tenantId?, action?, since?, limit, offset })`\n- Dynamically caches prepared statements by filter combination\n- Returns `AuditEvent[]` (raw DB rows with snake_case)\n\n---\n\n### 2. DATABASE LAYER\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\n**Files**:\n- `schema.ts` - Table definitions and migrations\n- `_helpers.ts` - Utilities (stmt cache, WHERE builder, row mappers)\n- `index.ts` - Barrel re-export\n- `personas.ts` - Persona CRUD\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential encryption/decryption\n- `events.ts` - Event publishing and subscriptions\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger scheduling\n- `executions.ts` - Execution CRUD and metrics\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Inference provider config\n\n**Database Library**: `better-sqlite3` (synchronous SQLite)\n\n**Prepared Statement Caching**:\n```typescript\n// WeakMap<Database, Map<sql, Statement>>\nfunction stmt(db, sql) {\n  // Compiled once per (db, sql) pair, cached forever\n}\n```\n\n**Row Mapper Pattern**:\n```typescript\nconst rowToExecution = createRowMapper<PersonaExecution>({\n  id: { col: 'id' },\n  projectId: { col: 'project_id', default: 'default' },\n  personaId: { col: 'persona_id' },\n  // ... field specs with bool, json, nullable, optional, default\n});\n```\nMaps snake_case DB columns to camelCase TypeScript fields.\n\n**Query Building**:\n```typescript\nbuildWhereClause(filters, columnMap)\n// Returns { sql: \"WHERE col1 = ? AND col2 = ?\", params: [val1, val2] }\n```\n\n**Key Tables**:\n\n1. **persona_executions**\n   - Tracks all model execution attempts\n   - Columns: id, project_id, persona_id, trigger_id, use_case_id, event_id, status, input_data, output_data, claude_session_id, model_used, input_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd, error_message, duration_ms, retry_of_execution_id, retry_count, started_at, completed_at, created_at\n   - Indexes: persona_id, status, (created_at, status)\n   - **Metrics recording**: On transition to terminal status (completed/failed/cancelled), increments `daily_metrics` table\n\n2. **persona_events**\n   - Event publishing system\n   - Status machine: pending → processing → (delivered|skipped|failed|partial|partial-retry)\n   - Columns: id, project_id, event_type, source_type, source_id, target_persona_id, payload, status, error_message, processed_at, use_case_id, retry_after, retry_count, created_at\n   - Indexes: status, (created_at, status)\n\n3. **daily_metrics** (tenant-level)\n   - Aggregates per day: total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms\n   - Uses UPSERT to increment on execution completion\n\n4. **system_daily_metrics** (system-level)\n   - Same schema as daily_metrics plus tenant_count, aggregated_at\n   - Populated by `aggregateSystemMetrics()` during daily retention run\n\n---\n\n### 3. HTTP API STRUCTURE\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts`\n\n**Route Types**:\n1. **Exact-path routes** - O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`\n2. **Resource routes** - O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`\n\n**Exact-Path Routes** (registered in `exactRoutes` Map):\n- `GET /api/status` - worker/queue/token status\n- `POST /api/execute` - queue execution (with HTTP audit)\n- `POST /api/gitlab/webhook` - webhook event ingestion\n- `GET /api/admin/users` - list tenant IDs (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/personas` - list all personas (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/executions` - list executions across tenants (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/audit` - query audit log (admin-only) with query params: `tenantId`, `action`, `since`, `limit`, `offset`\n- OAuth routes (delegated to `oauthHttpHandlers.ts`):\n  - `POST /api/oauth/authorize`\n  - `POST /api/oauth/callback`\n  - `GET /api/oauth/status`\n  - `POST /api/oauth/refresh`\n  - `DELETE /api/oauth/disconnect`\n  - `POST /api/token`\n\n**Resource Routes** (registered in `resourceRoutes` Map):\n\n| Method | Resource | Pattern | Handler |\n|--------|----------|---------|---------|\n| GET | personas | /api/personas | List summaries |\n| POST | personas | /api/personas | Create persona (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id} | /api/personas/{id} | Get full persona |\n| GET | personas/{id}/full | /api/personas/{id}/full | Hydrated persona |\n| DELETE | personas/{id} | /api/personas/{id} | Delete (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id}/tools | /api/personas/{id}/tools | List tools |\n| POST | personas/{id}/tools | /api/personas/{id}/tools | Link tool (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id}/credentials | /api/personas/{id}/credentials | List creds (redacted) |\n| POST | personas/{id}/credentials | /api/personas/{id}/credentials | Link credential |\n| GET | personas/{id}/subscriptions | /api/personas/{id}/subscriptions | List subscriptions |\n| GET | personas/{id}/triggers | /api/personas/{id}/triggers | List triggers (delegated) |\n| POST | tool-definitions | /api/tool-definitions | Create tool (with audit) |\n| POST | credentials | /api/credentials | Create credential (with audit) |\n| DELETE | credentials/{id} | /api/credentials/{id} | Delete credential (with audit) |\n| POST | subscriptions | /api/subscriptions | Create subscription (with audit) |\n| PUT | subscriptions/{id} | /api/subscriptions/{id} | Update subscription |\n| DELETE | subscriptions/{id} | /api/subscriptions/{id} | Delete subscription |\n| POST | triggers | /api/triggers | Create trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| PUT | triggers/{id} | /api/triggers/{id} | Update trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| DELETE | triggers/{id} | /api/triggers/{id} | Delete trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| GET | events | /api/events | List events |\n| POST | events | /api/events | Publish event (with audit) |\n| PUT | events/{id} | /api/events/{id} | Update event status (with audit) |\n| POST | webhooks/{id} | /api/webhooks/{id} | Receive webhook (with audit) |\n| GET | executions | /api/executions | List executions |\n| GET | executions/{id} | /api/executions/{id} | Get execution |\n| POST | executions/{id}/cancel | /api/executions/{id}/cancel | Cancel execution |\n\n**HTTP Audit Wrapper**:\n```typescript\nfunction withHttpAudit(handler, action, resourceType): RouteHandler {\n  // Executes handler, then on 2xx response, records audit event:\n  // { action, tenantId, actor, resourceType, resourceId, ipAddress }\n}\n```\n\n**Response Format Convention**:\n```typescript\nfunction json(res, status, data) {\n  res.writeHead(status, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n  res.end(JSON.stringify(data));\n}\n```\nAll responses are JSON. Errors use `{ error: string, reqId?: string }` format.\n\n**Request Body Handling**:\n```typescript\nfunction readBody(req): Promise<string> {\n  // Collects chunks, enforces 1MB limit, throws 'Payload too large'\n}\n```\n\n**Utility Helpers**:\n- `httpUtils.ts`: `json()`, `readBody()` with `MAX_BODY_BYTES = 1MB`\n- `triggerHttpHandlers.ts`: Routes POST/PUT/DELETE /api/triggers and GET /api/personas/{id}/triggers\n- `oauthHttpHandlers.ts`: Routes OAuth authorization, callback, status, refresh, disconnect, and token injection\n\n**Authentication**:\n- Validated by `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)` returning `RequestContext`\n- Checks Bearer token in Authorization header\n- Optional Supabase JWT in `x-user-token` header\n- Returns `{ authType: 'user' | 'admin', projectId, userEmail? }`\n- Admin-only routes checked with `requireAdmin(ctx, res)` (returns 403 if not admin)\n\n**Multi-tenancy**:\n- `tenantDbManager.getTenantDb(projectId)` resolves per-tenant database\n- User context scoped to their projectId, admin context gets `undefined` scope\n- `withScopedEntity()` enforces that projectId on entity matches request context\n\n---\n\n### 4. CONFIG SYSTEM\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n**OrchestratorConfig Interface**:\n```typescript\ninterface OrchestratorConfig {\n  // Auth\n  masterKey: string;                    // Required\n  claudeToken: string;                  // Optional, from setup\n  teamApiKey: string;                   // Required for API key validation\n  workerToken: string;                  // Required for worker auth\n  \n  // Kafka\n  kafkaBrokers: string;                 // Optional, default ''\n  kafkaUsername: string;                // Optional\n  kafkaPassword: string;                // Optional\n  kafkaEnabled: boolean;                // Computed from kafkaBrokers\n  \n  // JWT\n  supabaseJwtSecret: string;            // Optional for user-scoped auth\n  \n  // Networking\n  wsPort: number;                       // Worker WebSocket, default 8443\n  httpPort: number;                     // HTTP API, default 3001\n  \n  // TLS\n  tlsEnabled: boolean;                  // Default true\n  tlsCertPath: string;\n  tlsKeyPath: string;\n  tlsCaPath: string;\n  tlsRequireClientCert: boolean;\n  \n  // Scrubbing\n  scrubberEnabled: boolean;             // Default true\n  \n  // Audit\n  auditDbPath: string;                  // Default: dataDir/audit.db\n  auditRetentionDays: number;           // Default: 90, min enforced by spec\n  \n  // Data retention\n  retentionDays: number;                // Default: 30\n  metricsRetentionDays: number;         // Default: 365\n  \n  // Paths\n  dataDir: string;                      // Default: process.cwd()/data\n  \n  // Worker verification\n  allowedImageDigests: string[];        // CSV, optional\n  rejectUnverifiedWorkers: boolean;     // Default false\n}\n```\n\n**Loading Strategy**:\n- Environment variables with fallbacks\n- `required()` throws if missing\n- `optional(name, fallback)` returns value or fallback\n- Uses `dotenv/config` at top of file for .env support\n\n---\n\n### 5. EXISTING STATS/METRICS PATTERNS\n\n**Execution Metrics** (`packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts`):\n```typescript\n// On transition to terminal status, UPSERTs daily_metrics:\nINSERT INTO daily_metrics \n  (date, total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms)\nVALUES (?, 1, ?, ?, ?, ?)\nON CONFLICT(date) DO UPDATE SET\n  total_executions = total_executions + 1,\n  completed = completed + excluded.completed,\n  failed = failed + excluded.failed,\n  total_cost_usd = total_cost_usd + excluded.total_cost_usd,\n  total_duration_ms = total_duration_ms + excluded.total_duration_ms\n```\n\n**daily_metrics Table Schema** (per-tenant):\n```\ndate TEXT PRIMARY KEY (YYYY-MM-DD format)\ntotal_executions INTEGER (count)\ncompleted INTEGER (count of successful)\nfailed INTEGER (count of failed)\ntotal_cost_usd REAL (aggregated)\ntotal_duration_ms INTEGER (aggregated)\n```\n\n**system_daily_metrics Table Schema** (system-level):\n```\ndate TEXT PRIMARY KEY\ntotal_executions INTEGER\ncompleted INTEGER\nfailed INTEGER\ntotal_cost_usd REAL\ntotal_duration_ms REAL\ntenant_count INTEGER (number of active tenants that day)\naggregated_at TEXT (ISO timestamp of aggregation)\n```\n\n**Aggregation Process** (`packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`):\n```typescript\n// Daily job runs wall-clock time (once per UTC day)\n// 1. Purges old persona_executions, persona_events per retentionDays\n// 2. Aggregates: reads daily_metrics from all tenant DBs\n// 3. Combines: sums metrics per date across all tenants\n// 4. Writes: upserts aggregated row to system_daily_metrics\n\naggregateSystemMetrics(tenantDbManager, logger) {\n  const dayMap = new Map<date, { total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms, tenant_count }>();\n  // Loop each tenant, read daily_metrics, accumulate by date\n  // Upsert all accumulated rows into system_daily_metrics\n}\n```\n\n**Retention Hooks** (`packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`):\n```typescript\nTABLE_REGISTRY = [\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n    table: 'persona_executions',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    metrizableColumns: [\n      { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    ],\n    aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n  // ... ephemeral specs (no aggregation)\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. SHARED TYPES\n\n**File**: `packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n\n**Core Domain Types**:\n\n1. **Persona**\n   - Full model: id, projectId, name, description, systemPrompt, structuredPrompt, icon, color, enabled, maxConcurrent, timeoutMs, inferenceProfileId, networkPolicy, maxBudgetUsd, maxTurns, designContext, groupId, createdAt, updatedAt\n   - PersonaSummary: Lightweight projection (omits systemPrompt, structuredPrompt, etc.)\n\n2. **PersonaToolDefinition**\n   - id, name, category, description, scriptPath, inputSchema, outputSchema, requiresCredentialType, implementationGuide, isBuiltin, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n3. **PersonaCredential**\n   - id, projectId, name, serviceType, encryptedData, iv, tag, metadata, lastUsedAt, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n4. **PersonaEvent**\n   - Status machine: 'pending' → 'processing' → ('delivered'|'skipped'|'failed'|'partial'|'partial-retry')\n   - Columns: id, projectId, eventType, sourceType, sourceId, targetPersonaId, payload, status, errorMessage, processedAt, useCaseId, retryAfter, retryCount, createdAt\n\n5. **PersonaExecution**\n   - id, projectId, personaId, triggerId, useCaseId, eventId (for bidirectional tracing), status, inputData, outputData, claudeSessionId, modelUsed, inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, errorMessage, durationMs, retryOfExecutionId, retryCount, startedAt, completedAt, createdAt\n\n6. **PersonaTrigger**\n   - TriggerType: 'manual'|'schedule'|'polling'|'webhook'|'chain'\n   - Config: Discriminated union per trigger type (ScheduleTriggerConfig, ManualTriggerConfig, etc.)\n   - Columns: id, personaId, triggerType, config (JSON string), enabled, lastTriggeredAt, nextTriggerAt, useCaseId, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n---\n\n### 7. DATABASE QUERY PATTERNS\n\n**Prepared Statement Caching**:\nAll queries use the cached `stmt()` helper to avoid recompilation:\n```typescript\nstmt(db, 'SELECT * FROM personas WHERE id = ?').get(id)\n```\n\n**Transaction Support**:\n```typescript\ndb.transaction((entries, hashes) => {\n  for (let i = 0; i < entries.length; i++) {\n    stmt.run(...);  // All execute in single transaction\n  }\n})();\n```\n\n**Dynamic WHERE Clauses**:\n```typescript\nbuildWhereClause(\n  { projectId: scopedProjectId, personaId, status },\n  { projectId: 'project_id', personaId: 'persona_id', status: 'status' }\n);\n// Returns: { sql: \"WHERE project_id = ? AND status = ?\", params: [val, val] }\n```\n\n**Bulk Operations**:\n```typescript\n// Batch insert with transaction\nconst placeholders = personaIds.map(() => '?').join(',');\ndb.prepare(\n  `SELECT persona_id, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM persona_executions \n   WHERE persona_id IN (${placeholders}) AND status = 'running' \n   GROUP BY persona_id`\n).all(...personaIds)\n```\n\n**Chunked Deletions** (for large purges):\n```typescript\nwhile (true) {\n  const result = deleteStmt.run(cutoff, chunkSize);\n  if (result.changes < chunkSize) break;\n  await setImmediate();  // Yield event loop\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. AUTHORIZATION PATTERNS FOR ADMIN ENDPOINTS\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/auth.ts`\n\n**Two-Factor Auth**:\n1. **API Key** (Bearer token) - Always required\n   - Hashed with `hashApiKey()` and compared\n2. **Optional Supabase JWT** - In `x-user-token` header\n   - HS256 verification against `supabaseJwtSecret`\n   - Extracts `sub` (user UUID) and `email`\n\n**Context Extraction**:\n```typescript\nvalidateAndExtractContext(req) {\n  if (!validateApiKey(req)) return null;  // 401\n  \n  const userToken = req.headers['x-user-token'];\n  if (userToken && supabaseJwtSecret) {\n    const jwt = verifySupabaseJwt(userToken, supabaseJwtSecret);\n    if (jwt) return { authType: 'user', projectId: jwt.sub, userEmail: jwt.email };\n    return null;  // Invalid JWT → reject (don't fall back)\n  }\n  \n  // No JWT or disabled → admin context\n  return { authType: 'admin', projectId: '__admin__' };\n}\n```\n\n**Admin-Only Enforcement**:\n```typescript\nfunction requireAdmin(ctx, res) {\n  if (ctx.authType !== 'admin') {\n    res.writeHead(403, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Admin access required' }));\n    return true;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\n// In route handler:\nif (exactEntry.adminOnly && requireAdmin(ctx, res)) return;\n```\n\n**Admin Endpoints**:\n- `GET /api/admin/users` - List all tenant IDs\n- `GET /api/admin/personas` - List all personas across tenants\n- `GET /api/admin/executions` - List all executions with limit/offset\n- `GET /api/admin/audit` - Query audit log with optional filters\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHTS\n\n**Audit Event Flow**:\n1. Business logic triggers mutation\n2. `withHttpAudit()` wrapper executes handler\n3. On 2xx response, `auditLog.record(entry)` appends to buffer\n4. Buffer auto-flushes every 100ms or at 50 entries\n5. Batch flushes compute SHA-256 chain hashes and insert in transaction\n6. `prev_hash` column stores hash commitment to all prior history\n\n**HTTP Request Lifecycle**:\n1. Receive request → extract correlation ID\n2. Parse pathname & query params\n3. Check health endpoint (unauthenticated)\n4. Validate auth via `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)`\n5. Resolve tenant DB via `tenantDbManager.getTenantDb(projectId)`\n6. O(1) route lookup: exact-path routes → resource routes → 404\n7. Check `adminOnly` flag, tenant DB requirement\n8. Execute handler with scoped projectId\n9. Send response with X-Request-Id header\n\n**Multi-Tenancy**:\n- Each tenant has isolated SQLite DB: `dataDir/{projectId}/db.sqlite`\n- System DB tracks tenant registry and system-wide metrics\n- Admin context gets `projectId = '__admin__'` and `scopedProjectId = undefined` (sees all data)\n- User context scoped to their projectId\n- `withScopedEntity()` enforces entity.projectId matches request context\n\n**Metrics Pipeline**:\n1. **Execution completion** → increments `daily_metrics` (tenant-level)\n2. **Daily retention job** → reads all tenant `daily_metrics`\n3. **Aggregation** → sums by date across tenants\n4. **System write** → upserts `system_daily_metrics` (system-level)\n\n**Retention Safety**:\n- Uses `maxPurgeFraction` cap (default 0.8) to prevent accidental wipeouts\n- Chunked deletes (5000 rows per chunk) with event-loop yields between\n- Wall-clock daily scheduling (UTC-based) prevents drift\n- Persistence in `system_kv` table ensures \"runs once per day\" guarantee\n\n---\n\n### FILE LOCATIONS SUMMARY\n\n```\nC:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\\n\norchestrator/src/\n├── auditLog.ts                    # Append-only audit event DB\n├── auditPolicy.ts                 # Declarative event→audit mapper\n├── auditRetentionPolicy.ts        # Audit purge (≥90 days min)\n├── config.ts                      # OrchestratorConfig loading\n├── auth.ts                        # API key + JWT dual auth\n├── httpApi.ts                     # Main HTTP route handler\n├── httpUtils.ts                   # json(), readBody()\n├── oauthHttpHandlers.ts           # OAuth/token injection routes\n├── triggerHttpHandlers.ts         # Trigger CRUD routes\n├── retentionPolicy.ts             # Table lifecycle management (from TABLE_REGISTRY)\n├── retention.ts                   # Daily purge job + system metrics aggregation\n├── db/\n│   ├── schema.ts                  # Table definitions + migrations\n│   ├── _helpers.ts                # stmt cache, WHERE builder, row mappers\n│   ├── index.ts                   # Barrel export\n│   ├── executions.ts              # Execution CRUD + metrics recording\n│   ├── events.ts                  # Event publishing + subscriptions\n│   ├── personas.ts                # Persona CRUD\n│   ├── tools.ts                   # Tool definitions\n│   ├── credentials.ts             # Credential storage + encryption\n│   ├── triggers.ts                # Trigger config + scheduling\n│   └── inferenceProfiles.ts       # Inference provider config\n└── index.ts                       # Main entry point, component wiring\n\nshared/src/\n├── types.ts                       # Core domain types\n├── tableRegistry.ts               # TABLE_REGISTRY (metrizable/ephemeral specs)\n└── ... other shared files\n```\n\nThis is a comprehensive, well-architected system with clear patterns for audit logging, database access, HTTP routing, multi-tenancy, authentication, and metrics aggregation. All code follows consistent conventions for prepared statements, row mapping, audit recording, and error handling."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a11a2d6d686c90f56 (use SendMessage with to: 'a11a2d6d686c90f56' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 78173\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 82238</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2a8eabc1-ce20-4af0-9b5d-da3936e3656a","uuid":"e800ae44-b034-4f66-a1f9-821d15fb3efc","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:31:04.868Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The audit log system - look at packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts, auditPolicy.ts, auditRetentionPolicy.ts\n2. The database layer - look at packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory for all files, especially how queries are done\n3. The HTTP API - look at packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts and any HTTP handler files like oauthHttpHandlers.ts, triggerHttpHandlers.ts, httpUtils.ts\n4. The config - packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts\n5. Any existing stats/metrics/analytics patterns in the codebase\n6. The types - packages/shared/src/types.ts\n\nRead ALL of these files completely. I need to understand:\n- How audit events are stored (table schema, columns, indexes)\n- How HTTP endpoints are registered and structured\n- How database queries are written (what DB library is used)\n- Any existing aggregation/stats patterns\n- The response format conventions used by existing endpoints\n- How authentication/authorization is handled for admin endpoints","agentId":"a11a2d6d686c90f56","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored your codebase and compiled detailed findings across all the key systems you requested.\n\n### 1. AUDIT LOG SYSTEM\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/auditLog.ts`\n\n**Database Schema**:\n- Table: `audit_events` with columns:\n  - `id` (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n  - `timestamp` (TEXT NOT NULL) - ISO 8601 format\n  - `action` (TEXT NOT NULL) - string literal from AuditAction type\n  - `tenant_id` (TEXT) - optional tenant identifier\n  - `actor` (TEXT) - user email or projectId\n  - `resource_type` (TEXT) - entity type being audited\n  - `resource_id` (TEXT) - ID of affected resource\n  - `detail` (TEXT) - JSON-stringified detail object\n  - `ip_address` (TEXT) - remote IP from request\n  - `prev_hash` (TEXT) - SHA-256 chain hash for integrity verification\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_audit_ts` on `timestamp`\n- `idx_audit_tenant_action_ts` on `(tenant_id, action, timestamp)`\n\n**Key Features**:\n- **Buffered writes**: 50-entry buffer or 100ms flush interval (reduces fsync overhead)\n- **SHA-256 hash chain**: Each entry commits to entire history before it via `computeChainHash()`\n- **Genesis value**: 64 hex zeros for the first hash (deterministic)\n- **Chain verification**: `verify()` method validates entire chain integrity\n- **Migration support**: Auto-adds missing `prev_hash` column to existing DBs\n\n**Audit Entry Types** (discriminated union):\n- Key management: `key:encrypt`, `key:decrypt`, `key:decrypt_failed`, `key:delete`, `key:access`, `key:derive`\n- Personas: `persona:create`, `persona:delete`\n- Tools: `tool:link`, `tool-definition:create`\n- Credentials: `credential:link`\n- Subscriptions: `subscription:create`, `subscription:update`, `subscription:delete`\n- Workers: `worker:connected`, `worker:disconnected`\n- Triggers: `trigger:create`, `trigger:update`, `trigger:delete`\n- Events: `event:publish`, `event:update`\n- Executions: `execution:submit`\n- Webhooks: `webhook:receive`\n\n**Query Method**: `query({ tenantId?, action?, since?, limit, offset })`\n- Dynamically caches prepared statements by filter combination\n- Returns `AuditEvent[]` (raw DB rows with snake_case)\n\n---\n\n### 2. DATABASE LAYER\n\n**Location**: `packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\n**Files**:\n- `schema.ts` - Table definitions and migrations\n- `_helpers.ts` - Utilities (stmt cache, WHERE builder, row mappers)\n- `index.ts` - Barrel re-export\n- `personas.ts` - Persona CRUD\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential encryption/decryption\n- `events.ts` - Event publishing and subscriptions\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger scheduling\n- `executions.ts` - Execution CRUD and metrics\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Inference provider config\n\n**Database Library**: `better-sqlite3` (synchronous SQLite)\n\n**Prepared Statement Caching**:\n```typescript\n// WeakMap<Database, Map<sql, Statement>>\nfunction stmt(db, sql) {\n  // Compiled once per (db, sql) pair, cached forever\n}\n```\n\n**Row Mapper Pattern**:\n```typescript\nconst rowToExecution = createRowMapper<PersonaExecution>({\n  id: { col: 'id' },\n  projectId: { col: 'project_id', default: 'default' },\n  personaId: { col: 'persona_id' },\n  // ... field specs with bool, json, nullable, optional, default\n});\n```\nMaps snake_case DB columns to camelCase TypeScript fields.\n\n**Query Building**:\n```typescript\nbuildWhereClause(filters, columnMap)\n// Returns { sql: \"WHERE col1 = ? AND col2 = ?\", params: [val1, val2] }\n```\n\n**Key Tables**:\n\n1. **persona_executions**\n   - Tracks all model execution attempts\n   - Columns: id, project_id, persona_id, trigger_id, use_case_id, event_id, status, input_data, output_data, claude_session_id, model_used, input_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd, error_message, duration_ms, retry_of_execution_id, retry_count, started_at, completed_at, created_at\n   - Indexes: persona_id, status, (created_at, status)\n   - **Metrics recording**: On transition to terminal status (completed/failed/cancelled), increments `daily_metrics` table\n\n2. **persona_events**\n   - Event publishing system\n   - Status machine: pending → processing → (delivered|skipped|failed|partial|partial-retry)\n   - Columns: id, project_id, event_type, source_type, source_id, target_persona_id, payload, status, error_message, processed_at, use_case_id, retry_after, retry_count, created_at\n   - Indexes: status, (created_at, status)\n\n3. **daily_metrics** (tenant-level)\n   - Aggregates per day: total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms\n   - Uses UPSERT to increment on execution completion\n\n4. **system_daily_metrics** (system-level)\n   - Same schema as daily_metrics plus tenant_count, aggregated_at\n   - Populated by `aggregateSystemMetrics()` during daily retention run\n\n---\n\n### 3. HTTP API STRUCTURE\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts`\n\n**Route Types**:\n1. **Exact-path routes** - O(1) lookup by `METHOD:/path`\n2. **Resource routes** - O(1) lookup by `METHOD:resource[:id][:subResource]`\n\n**Exact-Path Routes** (registered in `exactRoutes` Map):\n- `GET /api/status` - worker/queue/token status\n- `POST /api/execute` - queue execution (with HTTP audit)\n- `POST /api/gitlab/webhook` - webhook event ingestion\n- `GET /api/admin/users` - list tenant IDs (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/personas` - list all personas (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/executions` - list executions across tenants (admin-only)\n- `GET /api/admin/audit` - query audit log (admin-only) with query params: `tenantId`, `action`, `since`, `limit`, `offset`\n- OAuth routes (delegated to `oauthHttpHandlers.ts`):\n  - `POST /api/oauth/authorize`\n  - `POST /api/oauth/callback`\n  - `GET /api/oauth/status`\n  - `POST /api/oauth/refresh`\n  - `DELETE /api/oauth/disconnect`\n  - `POST /api/token`\n\n**Resource Routes** (registered in `resourceRoutes` Map):\n\n| Method | Resource | Pattern | Handler |\n|--------|----------|---------|---------|\n| GET | personas | /api/personas | List summaries |\n| POST | personas | /api/personas | Create persona (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id} | /api/personas/{id} | Get full persona |\n| GET | personas/{id}/full | /api/personas/{id}/full | Hydrated persona |\n| DELETE | personas/{id} | /api/personas/{id} | Delete (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id}/tools | /api/personas/{id}/tools | List tools |\n| POST | personas/{id}/tools | /api/personas/{id}/tools | Link tool (with audit) |\n| GET | personas/{id}/credentials | /api/personas/{id}/credentials | List creds (redacted) |\n| POST | personas/{id}/credentials | /api/personas/{id}/credentials | Link credential |\n| GET | personas/{id}/subscriptions | /api/personas/{id}/subscriptions | List subscriptions |\n| GET | personas/{id}/triggers | /api/personas/{id}/triggers | List triggers (delegated) |\n| POST | tool-definitions | /api/tool-definitions | Create tool (with audit) |\n| POST | credentials | /api/credentials | Create credential (with audit) |\n| DELETE | credentials/{id} | /api/credentials/{id} | Delete credential (with audit) |\n| POST | subscriptions | /api/subscriptions | Create subscription (with audit) |\n| PUT | subscriptions/{id} | /api/subscriptions/{id} | Update subscription |\n| DELETE | subscriptions/{id} | /api/subscriptions/{id} | Delete subscription |\n| POST | triggers | /api/triggers | Create trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| PUT | triggers/{id} | /api/triggers/{id} | Update trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| DELETE | triggers/{id} | /api/triggers/{id} | Delete trigger (delegated, with audit) |\n| GET | events | /api/events | List events |\n| POST | events | /api/events | Publish event (with audit) |\n| PUT | events/{id} | /api/events/{id} | Update event status (with audit) |\n| POST | webhooks/{id} | /api/webhooks/{id} | Receive webhook (with audit) |\n| GET | executions | /api/executions | List executions |\n| GET | executions/{id} | /api/executions/{id} | Get execution |\n| POST | executions/{id}/cancel | /api/executions/{id}/cancel | Cancel execution |\n\n**HTTP Audit Wrapper**:\n```typescript\nfunction withHttpAudit(handler, action, resourceType): RouteHandler {\n  // Executes handler, then on 2xx response, records audit event:\n  // { action, tenantId, actor, resourceType, resourceId, ipAddress }\n}\n```\n\n**Response Format Convention**:\n```typescript\nfunction json(res, status, data) {\n  res.writeHead(status, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n  res.end(JSON.stringify(data));\n}\n```\nAll responses are JSON. Errors use `{ error: string, reqId?: string }` format.\n\n**Request Body Handling**:\n```typescript\nfunction readBody(req): Promise<string> {\n  // Collects chunks, enforces 1MB limit, throws 'Payload too large'\n}\n```\n\n**Utility Helpers**:\n- `httpUtils.ts`: `json()`, `readBody()` with `MAX_BODY_BYTES = 1MB`\n- `triggerHttpHandlers.ts`: Routes POST/PUT/DELETE /api/triggers and GET /api/personas/{id}/triggers\n- `oauthHttpHandlers.ts`: Routes OAuth authorization, callback, status, refresh, disconnect, and token injection\n\n**Authentication**:\n- Validated by `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)` returning `RequestContext`\n- Checks Bearer token in Authorization header\n- Optional Supabase JWT in `x-user-token` header\n- Returns `{ authType: 'user' | 'admin', projectId, userEmail? }`\n- Admin-only routes checked with `requireAdmin(ctx, res)` (returns 403 if not admin)\n\n**Multi-tenancy**:\n- `tenantDbManager.getTenantDb(projectId)` resolves per-tenant database\n- User context scoped to their projectId, admin context gets `undefined` scope\n- `withScopedEntity()` enforces that projectId on entity matches request context\n\n---\n\n### 4. CONFIG SYSTEM\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`\n\n**OrchestratorConfig Interface**:\n```typescript\ninterface OrchestratorConfig {\n  // Auth\n  masterKey: string;                    // Required\n  claudeToken: string;                  // Optional, from setup\n  teamApiKey: string;                   // Required for API key validation\n  workerToken: string;                  // Required for worker auth\n  \n  // Kafka\n  kafkaBrokers: string;                 // Optional, default ''\n  kafkaUsername: string;                // Optional\n  kafkaPassword: string;                // Optional\n  kafkaEnabled: boolean;                // Computed from kafkaBrokers\n  \n  // JWT\n  supabaseJwtSecret: string;            // Optional for user-scoped auth\n  \n  // Networking\n  wsPort: number;                       // Worker WebSocket, default 8443\n  httpPort: number;                     // HTTP API, default 3001\n  \n  // TLS\n  tlsEnabled: boolean;                  // Default true\n  tlsCertPath: string;\n  tlsKeyPath: string;\n  tlsCaPath: string;\n  tlsRequireClientCert: boolean;\n  \n  // Scrubbing\n  scrubberEnabled: boolean;             // Default true\n  \n  // Audit\n  auditDbPath: string;                  // Default: dataDir/audit.db\n  auditRetentionDays: number;           // Default: 90, min enforced by spec\n  \n  // Data retention\n  retentionDays: number;                // Default: 30\n  metricsRetentionDays: number;         // Default: 365\n  \n  // Paths\n  dataDir: string;                      // Default: process.cwd()/data\n  \n  // Worker verification\n  allowedImageDigests: string[];        // CSV, optional\n  rejectUnverifiedWorkers: boolean;     // Default false\n}\n```\n\n**Loading Strategy**:\n- Environment variables with fallbacks\n- `required()` throws if missing\n- `optional(name, fallback)` returns value or fallback\n- Uses `dotenv/config` at top of file for .env support\n\n---\n\n### 5. EXISTING STATS/METRICS PATTERNS\n\n**Execution Metrics** (`packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts`):\n```typescript\n// On transition to terminal status, UPSERTs daily_metrics:\nINSERT INTO daily_metrics \n  (date, total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms)\nVALUES (?, 1, ?, ?, ?, ?)\nON CONFLICT(date) DO UPDATE SET\n  total_executions = total_executions + 1,\n  completed = completed + excluded.completed,\n  failed = failed + excluded.failed,\n  total_cost_usd = total_cost_usd + excluded.total_cost_usd,\n  total_duration_ms = total_duration_ms + excluded.total_duration_ms\n```\n\n**daily_metrics Table Schema** (per-tenant):\n```\ndate TEXT PRIMARY KEY (YYYY-MM-DD format)\ntotal_executions INTEGER (count)\ncompleted INTEGER (count of successful)\nfailed INTEGER (count of failed)\ntotal_cost_usd REAL (aggregated)\ntotal_duration_ms INTEGER (aggregated)\n```\n\n**system_daily_metrics Table Schema** (system-level):\n```\ndate TEXT PRIMARY KEY\ntotal_executions INTEGER\ncompleted INTEGER\nfailed INTEGER\ntotal_cost_usd REAL\ntotal_duration_ms REAL\ntenant_count INTEGER (number of active tenants that day)\naggregated_at TEXT (ISO timestamp of aggregation)\n```\n\n**Aggregation Process** (`packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`):\n```typescript\n// Daily job runs wall-clock time (once per UTC day)\n// 1. Purges old persona_executions, persona_events per retentionDays\n// 2. Aggregates: reads daily_metrics from all tenant DBs\n// 3. Combines: sums metrics per date across all tenants\n// 4. Writes: upserts aggregated row to system_daily_metrics\n\naggregateSystemMetrics(tenantDbManager, logger) {\n  const dayMap = new Map<date, { total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms, tenant_count }>();\n  // Loop each tenant, read daily_metrics, accumulate by date\n  // Upsert all accumulated rows into system_daily_metrics\n}\n```\n\n**Retention Hooks** (`packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`):\n```typescript\nTABLE_REGISTRY = [\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n    table: 'persona_executions',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    metrizableColumns: [\n      { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    ],\n    aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n  // ... ephemeral specs (no aggregation)\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. SHARED TYPES\n\n**File**: `packages/shared/src/types.ts`\n\n**Core Domain Types**:\n\n1. **Persona**\n   - Full model: id, projectId, name, description, systemPrompt, structuredPrompt, icon, color, enabled, maxConcurrent, timeoutMs, inferenceProfileId, networkPolicy, maxBudgetUsd, maxTurns, designContext, groupId, createdAt, updatedAt\n   - PersonaSummary: Lightweight projection (omits systemPrompt, structuredPrompt, etc.)\n\n2. **PersonaToolDefinition**\n   - id, name, category, description, scriptPath, inputSchema, outputSchema, requiresCredentialType, implementationGuide, isBuiltin, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n3. **PersonaCredential**\n   - id, projectId, name, serviceType, encryptedData, iv, tag, metadata, lastUsedAt, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n4. **PersonaEvent**\n   - Status machine: 'pending' → 'processing' → ('delivered'|'skipped'|'failed'|'partial'|'partial-retry')\n   - Columns: id, projectId, eventType, sourceType, sourceId, targetPersonaId, payload, status, errorMessage, processedAt, useCaseId, retryAfter, retryCount, createdAt\n\n5. **PersonaExecution**\n   - id, projectId, personaId, triggerId, useCaseId, eventId (for bidirectional tracing), status, inputData, outputData, claudeSessionId, modelUsed, inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, errorMessage, durationMs, retryOfExecutionId, retryCount, startedAt, completedAt, createdAt\n\n6. **PersonaTrigger**\n   - TriggerType: 'manual'|'schedule'|'polling'|'webhook'|'chain'\n   - Config: Discriminated union per trigger type (ScheduleTriggerConfig, ManualTriggerConfig, etc.)\n   - Columns: id, personaId, triggerType, config (JSON string), enabled, lastTriggeredAt, nextTriggerAt, useCaseId, createdAt, updatedAt\n\n---\n\n### 7. DATABASE QUERY PATTERNS\n\n**Prepared Statement Caching**:\nAll queries use the cached `stmt()` helper to avoid recompilation:\n```typescript\nstmt(db, 'SELECT * FROM personas WHERE id = ?').get(id)\n```\n\n**Transaction Support**:\n```typescript\ndb.transaction((entries, hashes) => {\n  for (let i = 0; i < entries.length; i++) {\n    stmt.run(...);  // All execute in single transaction\n  }\n})();\n```\n\n**Dynamic WHERE Clauses**:\n```typescript\nbuildWhereClause(\n  { projectId: scopedProjectId, personaId, status },\n  { projectId: 'project_id', personaId: 'persona_id', status: 'status' }\n);\n// Returns: { sql: \"WHERE project_id = ? AND status = ?\", params: [val, val] }\n```\n\n**Bulk Operations**:\n```typescript\n// Batch insert with transaction\nconst placeholders = personaIds.map(() => '?').join(',');\ndb.prepare(\n  `SELECT persona_id, COUNT(*) as cnt FROM persona_executions \n   WHERE persona_id IN (${placeholders}) AND status = 'running' \n   GROUP BY persona_id`\n).all(...personaIds)\n```\n\n**Chunked Deletions** (for large purges):\n```typescript\nwhile (true) {\n  const result = deleteStmt.run(cutoff, chunkSize);\n  if (result.changes < chunkSize) break;\n  await setImmediate();  // Yield event loop\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. AUTHORIZATION PATTERNS FOR ADMIN ENDPOINTS\n\n**File**: `packages/orchestrator/src/auth.ts`\n\n**Two-Factor Auth**:\n1. **API Key** (Bearer token) - Always required\n   - Hashed with `hashApiKey()` and compared\n2. **Optional Supabase JWT** - In `x-user-token` header\n   - HS256 verification against `supabaseJwtSecret`\n   - Extracts `sub` (user UUID) and `email`\n\n**Context Extraction**:\n```typescript\nvalidateAndExtractContext(req) {\n  if (!validateApiKey(req)) return null;  // 401\n  \n  const userToken = req.headers['x-user-token'];\n  if (userToken && supabaseJwtSecret) {\n    const jwt = verifySupabaseJwt(userToken, supabaseJwtSecret);\n    if (jwt) return { authType: 'user', projectId: jwt.sub, userEmail: jwt.email };\n    return null;  // Invalid JWT → reject (don't fall back)\n  }\n  \n  // No JWT or disabled → admin context\n  return { authType: 'admin', projectId: '__admin__' };\n}\n```\n\n**Admin-Only Enforcement**:\n```typescript\nfunction requireAdmin(ctx, res) {\n  if (ctx.authType !== 'admin') {\n    res.writeHead(403, { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' });\n    res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Admin access required' }));\n    return true;\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\n// In route handler:\nif (exactEntry.adminOnly && requireAdmin(ctx, res)) return;\n```\n\n**Admin Endpoints**:\n- `GET /api/admin/users` - List all tenant IDs\n- `GET /api/admin/personas` - List all personas across tenants\n- `GET /api/admin/executions` - List all executions with limit/offset\n- `GET /api/admin/audit` - Query audit log with optional filters\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY ARCHITECTURAL INSIGHTS\n\n**Audit Event Flow**:\n1. Business logic triggers mutation\n2. `withHttpAudit()` wrapper executes handler\n3. On 2xx response, `auditLog.record(entry)` appends to buffer\n4. Buffer auto-flushes every 100ms or at 50 entries\n5. Batch flushes compute SHA-256 chain hashes and insert in transaction\n6. `prev_hash` column stores hash commitment to all prior history\n\n**HTTP Request Lifecycle**:\n1. Receive request → extract correlation ID\n2. Parse pathname & query params\n3. Check health endpoint (unauthenticated)\n4. Validate auth via `auth.validateAndExtractContext(req)`\n5. Resolve tenant DB via `tenantDbManager.getTenantDb(projectId)`\n6. O(1) route lookup: exact-path routes → resource routes → 404\n7. Check `adminOnly` flag, tenant DB requirement\n8. Execute handler with scoped projectId\n9. Send response with X-Request-Id header\n\n**Multi-Tenancy**:\n- Each tenant has isolated SQLite DB: `dataDir/{projectId}/db.sqlite`\n- System DB tracks tenant registry and system-wide metrics\n- Admin context gets `projectId = '__admin__'` and `scopedProjectId = undefined` (sees all data)\n- User context scoped to their projectId\n- `withScopedEntity()` enforces entity.projectId matches request context\n\n**Metrics Pipeline**:\n1. **Execution completion** → increments `daily_metrics` (tenant-level)\n2. **Daily retention job** → reads all tenant `daily_metrics`\n3. **Aggregation** → sums by date across tenants\n4. **System write** → upserts `system_daily_metrics` (system-level)\n\n**Retention Safety**:\n- Uses `maxPurgeFraction` cap (default 0.8) to prevent accidental wipeouts\n- Chunked deletes (5000 rows per chunk) with event-loop yields between\n- Wall-clock daily scheduling (UTC-based) prevents drift\n- Persistence in `system_kv` table ensures \"runs once per day\" guarantee\n\n---\n\n### FILE LOCATIONS SUMMARY\n\n```\nC:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\packages\\\n\norchestrator/src/\n├── auditLog.ts                    # Append-only audit event DB\n├── auditPolicy.ts                 # Declarative event→audit mapper\n├── auditRetentionPolicy.ts        # Audit purge (≥90 days min)\n├── config.ts                      # OrchestratorConfig loading\n├── auth.ts                        # API key + JWT dual auth\n├── httpApi.ts                     # Main HTTP route handler\n├── httpUtils.ts                   # json(), readBody()\n├── oauthHttpHandlers.ts           # OAuth/token injection routes\n├── triggerHttpHandlers.ts         # Trigger CRUD routes\n├── retentionPolicy.ts             # Table lifecycle management (from TABLE_REGISTRY)\n├── retention.ts                   # Daily purge job + system metrics aggregation\n├── db/\n│   ├── schema.ts                  # Table definitions + migrations\n│   ├── _helpers.ts                # stmt cache, WHERE builder, row mappers\n│   ├── index.ts                   # Barrel export\n│   ├── executions.ts              # Execution CRUD + metrics recording\n│   ├── events.ts                  # Event publishing + subscriptions\n│   ├── personas.ts                # Persona CRUD\n│   ├── tools.ts                   # Tool definitions\n│   ├── credentials.ts             # Credential storage + encryption\n│   ├── triggers.ts                # Trigger config + scheduling\n│   └── inferenceProfiles.ts       # Inference provider config\n└── index.ts                       # Main entry point, component wiring\n\nshared/src/\n├── types.ts                       # Core domain types\n├── tableRegistry.ts               # TABLE_REGISTRY (metrizable/ephemeral specs)\n└── ... other shared files\n```\n\nThis is a comprehensive, well-architected system with clear patterns for audit logging, database access, HTTP routing, multi-tenancy, authentication, and metrics aggregation. All code follows consistent conventions for prepared statements, row mapping, audit recording, and error handling."}],"totalDurationMs":82238,"totalTokens":78173,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3100,"cache_read_input_tokens":68369,"output_tokens":6699,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3100},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
